name: Lace Wrapped Painted Vintage Clothespins
description:
Totally shabby sweet! I've painted the vintage clothes pins in pink or blue and wrapped vintage lace around each, held on by a shiny little T pin. 

Pink clothespins: 1 yard (3 feet) each of white cotton lace & pink lace.
Blue clothespins: 1 yard (3 feet) each of white cotton lace and teal blue lace. 

Clothespins are 3 3/4" in length. Package of 1.

name: Distressed Cotton Ribbon-20mm
description:
Super fun, cotton woven 'ribbon', the edges are not finished and are slightly 'distressed' and wrinkly....just the way we like it! 

Available in 2 colours, Buttercup and Sky Blue...

20mm in width, available by the foot. 

please note that because the fabric is cut on the bias, there is a barely noticeable seam approximately every 5 feet.

name: Vintage Wallpaper Scrolls
description:
Nothing compares to vintage wallpaper, the texture, designs and colors. 

Choices include  brown & blue, blue & white, pink & green and brown & orange. 

All the papers have a matte finish. All papers are a single sheet, measuring 24" x 10.5". 

Comes rolled and tied with ribbon!

name: Cigar Tubes
description:
The potential is limitedless! Attach to a cord or chain through the screw on lid and stash secret items inside for a Talisman Necklace...add to an assemblage or use to store beads or buttons in. 

Each lightweight aluminum tube is approximately 5 1/4" long and nearly 1" in diameter, lid screws on and most (but not all) still have the strip of thin wood inside. 

***************************************
NOTE PLEASE! 
These use to contain real CIGARS and when you open them, you can smell the cigar smell. 
Please be aware in case you have an allergy or aversion to cigar smell. 
Closed up there is no smell (so you dont have to worry about your other items in the box smelling like cigar).

name: Shabby Paris Vintage Style Fabric Tags- Hand Stamped with Eyelet & String
description:
So many uses!!!! 

Tie around an altered shabby pretty bottle filled with vintage rhinestones or crystals, tie onto the next gift you give, add to your vintage style artwork or scrapbook, slip onto a jumpring and hang on a chain for a mixed media necklace.

(in one photo, I've used a regular art marker to write the "2" on the fabric tag, easy peasy!)

I've taken this simply scrummy vintage heavy fabric 'ribbon' (it's very thick and strong, more like canvas then ribbon) and hand stamped it with one of 4 design stamps in dark brown ink, added an eyelet in one corner and a long piece of white butchers twine. 

I leave the twine loose so you can use your own style of knot to tie it...

each tag is 3/4" wide and 2" long. 

Pick: 
1) Crown
2) Key
3) Moth
4) No. 

Price is per tag, you can always mix & match! 

{visit http://brendabraun.blogspot.com to see what I'm up to}
